ttps://www.argusleader.com/story/news/2020/03/10/south-dakota-coronavirus-update-first-case-covid-19/4999413002/ |title= South Dakota reports 5 'presumptive positive' cases of coronavirus with one death|work=[[Argus Leader]]|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref> March 13, Governor Noem declared a state of emergency; School are closed beginning March 16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/friday-covid-19-south-dakota-update-1-more-positive-case/|title=Noem signs State of Emergency order; Requests schools to close throughout South Dakota next week|date=March 13, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://siouxcityjournal.com/news/local/state-and-regional/noem-orders-south-dakota-k-12-schools-to-close-next-week-iowa-nebraska-holding-off/article_14ddb2a4-3a5d-5a1c-b467-eb3327f2392e.html|title=Noem orders South Dakota K-12 schools to close next week; Iowa, Nebraska holding off on similar moves|first=Bret|last=Hayworth|website=Sioux City Journal}}</ref>\n\nOn April 9, over 80 employees at a [[Smithfield Foods]] pork processing plant in [[Sioux Falls, South Dakota|Sioux Falls]] were confirmed to have COVID-19. The plant announced it would suspend operations beginning April 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/business/articles/2020-04-09/smithfield-temporarily-shuts-pork-plant-due-to-coronavirus|title=Smithfield Temporarily Shuts Pork Plant Due to Coronavirus|last=Associated Press|first=|date=2020-04-09|website=US News and World Report|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> By that day, Smithfield employees accounted for the majority of active cases in South Dakota. Some activity continued at the plant on April 14, as it planned to shut down completely.<ref>{{cite news |title=One of the largest pork processing facilities in the US is closing until further notice |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/12/business/meat-plant-closures-smithfield/index.html |accessdate=14 April 2020 |work=CNN}}</ref>\n\n=